# CURRENT PRIORITY — CC Chat OpenClaw Integration

## STOP. Read this first.

Your #1 priority right now is implementing the CC Chat ↔ OpenClaw Integration Spec.
Do NOT write tests, refactor utilities, or work on anything else until Phase 1 is complete.

**Spec:** `docs/CC-CHAT-OPENCLAW-INTEGRATION-SPEC.md` — read it fully before starting.

## Execution Order (STRICT)

1. Phase 1.1 — @Mention Routing (parseMentions + autocomplete + parallel dispatch)
2. Phase 1.2 — Group Chat Multi-Agent Response (replace random picker → parallel to all members)
3. Phase 1.3 — Typing Indicators (agent typing state while waiting for OpenClaw response)
4. Phase 1.4 — Delivery Status (sent/delivered/read checkmarks on user messages)
5. Phase 2 — Rich Media (reactions, file upload, pinned messages)
6. Phase 3 — Agent Push (webhook endpoint, agent status sync)
7. Phase 4 — Threading + Search

## Key Files

- Chat frontend: `src/app/command-center/chat/page.tsx`
- Chat API: `src/app/api/command-center/chat/route.ts`
- Gateway lib: `src/lib/openclaw-gateway.ts`
- Spec: `docs/CC-CHAT-OPENCLAW-INTEGRATION-SPEC.md`
- Status tracking: `docs/CC-IMPLEMENTATION-STATUS.md`

## Rules

- One sub-task at a time. Commit after each.
- Use existing design tokens from chat/page.tsx lines 13-62. No new colors.
- No dark mode changes. No new dependencies without justification.
- Update `docs/CC-IMPLEMENTATION-STATUS.md` after each phase completion.
- Follow the Parallax Protocol: start with the human, make complexity invisible, every pixel intentional.

## Design System (DO NOT DEVIATE)

- Background: `#0a0a0a` (main), `rgba(255,255,255,0.02)` (card)
- Borders: `#1e1e1e`
- Text: `#e5e5e5` (primary), `#888888` (secondary)
- Accent: `#7c3aed` (purple), `#C9A84C` (gold)
- Agent colors: `COLORS.agents[agentId]`
- Font: Inter, system-ui
